headline: BofA CFO Says Bank Among First Brands Lenders, Confident in Position
summary: Bank of America’s chief financial officer told reporters that the lender had worked on an asset-backed loan deal for the bankrupt auto-parts company First Brands.  “We’re in the syndicated loan for the First Brands deal,” Alastair Borthwick said in response to a question from Barron’s, adding, “when we think about prudent risk management, we're thinking about the borrower, we're thinking about the collateral, and here, we're secured.”  A spokeswoman for Bank of America declined to specify the impact the work for First Brands had on quarterly earnings.

headline: Bank of America Stock Jumps as Key Net Interest Income Outlook Raised
summary: Bank of America said Wednesday it now expects to drive more net interest income, or NII, this year than it initially forecast.  Bank of America said higher loan and deposit balances and activity across its global markets business helped drive third-quarter NII higher by 9% to a record $15.4 billion on a fully taxable-equivalent basis.  Net interest income is the difference between what lenders earn on interest-bearing assets, like loans, and what they pay back out to customers in interest.

headline: Bank of America Profit Jumps 23%
summary: Bank of America’s third-quarter profit rose 23% from a year ago to $8.5 billion, the company said Wednesday, rounding out a series of earnings reports from the largest U.S. banks this week.  A year ago, the bank reported net income of $6.9 billion, or per-share earnings of 81 cents, on revenue of $25.3 billion. content.title: Bank of America Profit Jumps 23%
content.summary: Bank of America’s third-quarter profit rose 23% from a year ago to $8.5 billion, the company said Wednesday, rounding out a series of earnings reports from the largest U.S. banks this week.  A year ago, the bank reported net income of $6.9 billion, or per-share earnings of 81 cents, on revenue of $25.3 billion.  Bank of America’s net interest income, a key revenue source, rose 9% from a year earlier to $15.2 billion.
